# Development: omit VITE_API_URL — same-origin /api on :3000 is proxied to backend (backend/.env PORT, default 4000).
# If you set VITE_DEV_API_PORT, it must match backend PORT.
# `npm run dev` — waits for /api/health, auto-starts backend if needed, then Vite. `npm run dev:vite-only` — Vite only (API may lag).
# `npm run dev:no-auto-api` — wait for API, do not spawn. `npm run dev:wait-api` — wait then Vite (no spawn).

# Production: required before npm run build
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
